post_text:
While we have focused our attention to the health and safety of all students during this pandemic, much of our thoughts have been with the senior class.

We wanted to find a way to honor seniors for the hard work they have put in over the last 12 years. So today we held a Class of 2020 Caravan, where we visited each senior at home (from as safe distance!) and provided them with t-shirts and yard signs! We thank the Cayuga County Sheriffs Office and the Cato Fire Department for escorting us throughout the district!

Seniors, we know this is a tough time. But just remember, "Tough times go away, tough people do not." We miss you and hope today made you as happy as it made us!

post_text:
Good afternoon everyone! Our counselors wanted to share the following message!!

Hello Cato-Meridian Friends and Family!

This school closure can bring on lots of different emotions: some of us might be getting bored and stir crazy, some of us might be worried and have questions that no one has the answers to. Others might be grateful for the extra time home with our families while some of us might be ready for a change in scenery!

There is not a right or wrong way to feel while we are self-quarantined and social distancing. Here's some things you and your family can practice to manage your emotional health while you're home.

Feel free to post pictures or videos showing which strategies you're practicing and tag us! Stay safe and healthy!
text:
Good afternoon everyone! Our counselors wanted to share the following message!!

Hello Cato-Meridian Friends and Family!

This school closure can bring on lots of different emotions: some of us might be getting bored and stir crazy, some of us might be worried and have questions that no one has the answers to. Others might be grateful for the extra time home with our families while some of us might be ready for a change in scenery!

There is not a right or wrong way to feel while we are self-quarantined and social distancing. Here's some things you and your family can practice to manage your emotional health while you're home.

Feel free to post pictures or videos showing which strategies you're practicing and tag us! Stay safe and healthy!

post_text:
Good Afternoon! Please review the message below from Superintendent Ward related to the upcoming shipment of our Care Baskets!

For those students who need paper academic materials they will be delivered Thursday morning starting at 10:00 AM.
Also, we have developed "Care Baskets" for every student at Cato-Meridian. I want you to know we have taken extreme safety measures to make sure the Care Baskets are safe.

The safety measures include:

*Care Baskets prepared by adults who wore masks and gloves
*Care Baskets populated with candy straight out of the plastic package
*Care Baskets sprayed in a room with hospital grade disinfectant
*Care Baskets (paper bag) made by homeroom teachers two days prior to delivery
*Deliveries made with adults wearing masks
*Practicing six-foot social distancing during delivery

Care Baskets were made with positive messages by each homeroom teacher. We hope the Care Baskets will lift the spirits of our kids! We hope you enjoy the them!

Dr. Terry L. Ward

For the 2020-2021 school year the Cato-Meridian Central School District is transitioning to full day Pre-K! The registration date for Pre-K is March 18. If have questions about Pre-K registration please contact 315-626-2293.

Full day Pre-K is part of the 2020-2021 school budget proposal. More information about the entire 2020-2021 school budget will be available later this Spring. Please remember budget vote day on May 19th. Thank you!
